reviews.review_text: Great recording - hot show! Found this apparent matrix recording today and thought I'd give it a try. Haven't finished the whole thing yet, but so far so good.  There are a few sour notes during Jack Straw but Jerry makes up for it during Suragee.  Try it you'll like it!

a bit overrated I do think this show has some special moments and certainly a desire, but it really just doesn't seem as 'on' as so many others. But so many love this one (as do so many the cornell 77).

Great show, fair recording My 3rd and probably favorite Dead show. Took off on Sugaree and never stopped.  But the quality is lacking compared to some other 1979 shows (May 9 Binghamton comes to mind).

I've seen it noted here before under a different Pittsburgh show, but there is a general lack of quality recordings of Pittsburgh shows.

Althea All time favorite Althea.Just long and mellow with a super hot theme about it. Many go to this show to hear the Glory jam and first CC rider but this  A L T H E A. Is where its at for me. sounds pretty good also
- Best AUD of an excellent show.
